# Cloudflare Pages routing. Vite's `public/` is copied verbatim into dist/.
#
# The app itself (/app/*, /signin, /onboarding, /accept-invite/*) is a pure
# client-side SPA — no prerendered file exists for e.g. /app/today, so
# without this it would fall through to 404.html (which now exists because
# Pillar 5 added a real one; Pages' old default "no 404.html → fall back to
# index.html for everything" behavior no longer applies). Every OTHER path
# either has a real prerendered file (marketing pages, legal pages) or is a
# genuine 404 — those are deliberately NOT redirected here, so 404.html
# still does its job.
/app/*            /index.html   200
/signin           /index.html   200
/onboarding       /index.html   200
/accept-invite/*  /index.html   200
